WEBVTT

00:00:01.840 --> 00:00:06.540
Do you have relatives that are presently not serving Jehovah?

00:00:06.540 --> 00:00:10.339
I think most of us do, and we're not alone.

00:00:10.339 --> 00:00:14.140
Even our Lord Jesus had that same circumstance.

00:00:14.140 --> 00:00:19.140
Even though His half-brothers knew about the miracles He was performing,

00:00:19.140 --> 00:00:26.640
the Bible says that they were not expressing faith in Jesus as the Messiah.

00:00:26.940 --> 00:00:32.340
Well, it was so bad, can you imagine, that when Jesus was being put to death,

00:00:32.340 --> 00:00:34.939
it appears that His brothers were not there.

00:00:34.939 --> 00:00:38.939
Do you remember the account where Jesus was on the torture stake

00:00:38.939 --> 00:00:43.439
and He looked down at the disciple and asked Him, basically,

00:00:43.439 --> 00:00:46.340
to become responsible for His mother?

00:00:46.340 --> 00:00:49.740
They weren't there to support Him.

00:00:49.740 --> 00:00:55.740
But what happened just a short while after Jesus had been resurrected?

00:00:55.740 --> 00:01:01.039
Well, it was amazing because some of those half-brothers were found,

00:01:01.039 --> 00:01:06.239
along with Jesus' mother, with the disciples fervently praying.

00:01:06.239 --> 00:01:09.040
Can you imagine how Jesus must have felt?

00:01:09.040 --> 00:01:16.340
Can you imagine the joy He must have experienced to see them now beginning to express faith?

00:01:16.340 --> 00:01:19.540
Well, maybe you've had that experience, too.

00:01:19.540 --> 00:01:23.540
Maybe one of your relatives, maybe your mate, one of your children,

00:01:23.540 --> 00:01:27.640
one of your siblings, has now come to serve Jehovah.

00:01:27.640 --> 00:01:33.439
How wonderful, what a joyful feeling, really nothing could compare to it.

00:01:33.439 --> 00:01:39.739
Well, what was it that helped Jesus' half-brothers to go from being faithless

00:01:39.739 --> 00:01:41.540
to putting faith in Him?

00:01:41.540 --> 00:01:45.640
And what can you and I learn from that example?

00:01:45.640 --> 00:01:47.640
Well, let's address that question.

00:01:47.640 --> 00:01:52.640
What was it that helped Jesus' brothers to acquire faith?

00:01:52.640 --> 00:01:55.439
Well, here's the number one thing.

00:01:55.439 --> 00:01:59.840
Jesus was patient with His relatives.

00:01:59.840 --> 00:02:05.640
Now, that's an important point because look at how Jesus was treated by His relatives.

00:02:05.640 --> 00:02:11.039
Would you look with me at Mark chapter 3 and verse 21?

00:02:11.039 --> 00:02:15.639
It says there, but when His relatives heard about it,

00:02:15.639 --> 00:02:22.840
they went out to seize Him, for they were saying He has gone out of His mind.

00:02:22.840 --> 00:02:27.840
Jesus did not take offense, even though His relatives were trying to seize Him,

00:02:27.840 --> 00:02:31.139
even though they said He had gone crazy.

00:02:31.139 --> 00:02:35.340
Have your relatives perhaps said some things like that to you?

00:02:35.340 --> 00:02:39.639
Jesus did not take offense, He was patient.

00:02:39.639 --> 00:02:44.439
Well, in fact, after His resurrection, look what Jesus did.

00:02:44.439 --> 00:02:49.939
Let's go to 1 Corinthians chapter 15 and let's read together verse 7.

00:02:49.939 --> 00:02:57.639
It says, after that, He appeared to James, then to all the apostles.

00:02:57.639 --> 00:03:02.039
Now, this is just a very small detail, but did you notice what it said?

00:03:02.039 --> 00:03:05.340
So Jesus appeared to James.

00:03:05.340 --> 00:03:10.539
Well, now, we don't know what Jesus said to James when He appeared to him,

00:03:10.639 --> 00:03:18.340
but the point is that Jesus made a special effort to appear to His half-brother James.

00:03:18.340 --> 00:03:24.139
Well, James must have deeply appreciated that special attention from Jesus.

00:03:24.139 --> 00:03:25.939
And why do we say that?

00:03:25.939 --> 00:03:33.539
Well, Jesus, excuse me, James went on to become a respected elder in the congregation in Jerusalem.

00:03:33.539 --> 00:03:37.139
In fact, you may remember that in Acts chapter 15,

00:03:37.139 --> 00:03:43.439
when the apostles and older men gathered in Jerusalem to consider the matter about circumcision,

00:03:43.439 --> 00:03:48.840
it seems that James was the one who was presiding at that meeting.

00:03:48.840 --> 00:03:51.039
Well, what had happened?

00:03:51.039 --> 00:03:58.840
James had gone from being a faithless person to now being a pillar in the congregation.

00:03:58.840 --> 00:04:05.039
James and his other half-brother Jude both had the privilege of writing letters

00:04:05.039 --> 00:04:09.340
that were included in the Christian Greek scriptures.

00:04:09.340 --> 00:04:22.139
When I'm in the following video, please take careful note of what helped a family member to be a person with faith.

00:04:22.139 --> 00:04:25.639
The truth came to our home through my mother.

00:04:25.639 --> 00:04:29.339
I was never seriously interested in the truth.

00:04:29.339 --> 00:04:32.839
Where we grew up, education was very important.

00:04:32.839 --> 00:04:37.339
My person needed to make money and live a lavish life.

00:04:37.339 --> 00:04:45.139
So that's the life I chose to study, to get higher education so that I could have what others had.

00:04:45.139 --> 00:04:51.839
Although they could see that I wasn't interested in the truth, my mother and brother did not give up on me.

00:04:51.839 --> 00:04:59.339
When I came back from school in January, my mother ordered the examining the scriptures daily booklet for me.

00:04:59.339 --> 00:05:06.339
The year after year, I always had the examining the scriptures daily booklet and the Bible.

00:05:06.339 --> 00:05:13.350
She made sure that although I wasn't attending meetings, at least I had literature.

00:05:13.350 --> 00:05:21.850
Besides that, my younger brother, the one I was close to, decided to take the truth seriously.

00:05:21.850 --> 00:05:26.850
When I came back from school, I saw my brother getting a Bible study of his own.

00:05:26.850 --> 00:05:32.850
And I was surprised to see him studying the Bible and noticed that he had prepared.

00:05:32.850 --> 00:05:36.850
He cared about and loved what he was learning.

00:05:36.850 --> 00:05:41.850
That's when I understood that the Bible changes lives.

00:05:41.850 --> 00:05:48.850
A scripture that comes to mind is Hosea 11 verse 4.

00:05:48.850 --> 00:05:54.850
There it shows that Jehovah pulls us with cords of love and kindness.

00:05:54.850 --> 00:05:58.850
In my situation, Jehovah did this.

00:05:58.850 --> 00:06:03.850
So I made the decision to be regular at the congregation meetings.

00:06:03.850 --> 00:06:10.850
And I finally started studying the Bible with someone in 2007 and got baptized in 2008.

00:06:10.850 --> 00:06:15.850
My family really encouraged me. They never gave up on me.

00:06:15.850 --> 00:06:19.850
And I encouraged parents not to give up on their children.

00:06:19.850 --> 00:06:31.100
They must continue encouraging them and have the hope that Jehovah God will draw them to the organization because they have good hearts.

00:06:31.100 --> 00:06:40.230
Well, brothers and sisters, we want that same experience for our relatives.

00:06:40.230 --> 00:06:45.230
What can we do to help them to grow in faith?

00:06:45.230 --> 00:06:50.230
Well, let's talk briefly about three things. Here's the first one.

00:06:50.230 --> 00:06:54.230
Be patient with your relatives.

00:06:54.230 --> 00:06:58.230
We want to imitate the example of our wonderful God, Jehovah.

00:06:58.230 --> 00:07:03.230
Do you remember when the nation of Israel went to stray so many times?

00:07:03.230 --> 00:07:11.230
Well, in Jeremiah chapter 44, the Bible says that Jehovah sent his prophets again and again.

00:07:11.230 --> 00:07:15.230
He was very patient with his people.

00:07:15.230 --> 00:07:20.230
We want to be patient with our relatives too. Don't give up on them.

00:07:20.230 --> 00:07:24.230
And then second, we want to be tactful.

00:07:24.230 --> 00:07:29.230
We want to look for ways that we can stimulate their interest in the truth.

00:07:29.230 --> 00:07:36.230
It's true. Jesus described the message of the truth like water that could lead to everlasting life.

00:07:36.230 --> 00:07:40.230
